    "Absolutely buddy — here’s the full explanation of TP, TN, FP, FN with clear examples.\n",
    "\n",
    "Confusion Matrix Basics\n",
    "\n",
    "In a binary classification problem, predictions usually have two classes:\n",
    "\n",
    "Positive\n",
    "\n",
    "Negative\n",
    "\n",
    "For example:\n",
    "\n",
    "Disease / No Disease\n",
    "\n",
    "Fraud / Not Fraud\n",
    "\n",
    "Spam / Not Spam\n",
    "\n",
    "Pass / Fail\n",
    "\n",
    "When the model predicts, there are 4 possible outcomes:\n",
    "\n",
    "True Positive (TP)\n",
    "\n",
    "True Negative (TN)\n",
    "\n",
    "False Positive (FP)\n",
    "\n",
    "False Negative (FN)\n",
    "\n",
    "These 4 together form the confusion matrix.\n",
    "\n",
    "1) True Positive (TP)\n",
    "Meaning\n",
    "\n",
    "The model predicted Positive, and the actual result is also Positive.\n",
    "\n",
    "So the model is correct.\n",
    "\n",
    "Formula idea\n",
    "\n",
    "Predicted = Positive\n",
    "Actual = Positive\n",
    "\n",
    "Example: Disease Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "Actual: Person has disease\n",
    "\n",
    "Predicted: Model says disease is present\n",
    "\n",
    "This is True Positive\n",
    "\n",
    "More examples\n",
    "\n",
    "Spam email is actually spam, and model marks it as spam\n",
    "\n",
    "Fraud transaction is actually fraud, and model detects fraud\n",
    "\n",
    "Student actually passed, and model predicts pass\n",
    "\n",
    "2) True Negative (TN)\n",
    "Meaning\n",
    "\n",
    "The model predicted Negative, and the actual result is also Negative.\n",
    "\n",
    "So again, the model is correct.\n",
    "\n",
    "Formula idea\n",
    "\n",
    "Predicted = Negative\n",
    "Actual = Negative\n",
    "\n",
    "Example: Disease Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "Actual: Person does not have disease\n",
    "\n",
    "Predicted: Model says no disease\n",
    "\n",
    "This is True Negative\n",
    "\n",
    "More examples\n",
    "\n",
    "Genuine email is marked as not spam\n",
    "\n",
    "Normal transaction is marked as not fraud\n",
    "\n",
    "Student actually failed, and model predicts fail\n",
    "\n",
    "3) False Positive (FP)\n",
    "Meaning\n",
    "\n",
    "The model predicted Positive, but the actual result is Negative.\n",
    "\n",
    "So the model gave a wrong alarm.\n",
    "\n",
    "Formula idea\n",
    "\n",
    "Predicted = Positive\n",
    "Actual = Negative\n",
    "\n",
    "Example: Disease Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "Actual: Person is healthy\n",
    "\n",
    "Predicted: Model says person has disease\n",
    "\n",
    "This is False Positive\n",
    "\n",
    "Why called false positive?\n",
    "\n",
    "Because the model said “positive,” but that was false.\n",
    "\n",
    "More examples\n",
    "\n",
    "Genuine email is marked as spam\n",
    "\n",
    "Normal transaction is marked as fraud\n",
    "\n",
    "Innocent person is incorrectly flagged by facial recognition\n",
    "\n",
    "4) False Negative (FN)\n",
    "Meaning\n",
    "\n",
    "The model predicted Negative, but the actual result is Positive.\n",
    "\n",
    "So the model missed a real positive case.\n",
    "\n",
    "Formula idea\n",
    "\n",
    "Predicted = Negative\n",
    "Actual = Positive\n",
    "\n",
    "Example: Disease Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "Actual: Person has disease\n",
    "\n",
    "Predicted: Model says no disease\n",
    "\n",
    "This is False Negative\n",
    "\n",
    "Why called false negative?\n",
    "\n",
    "Because the model said “negative,” but that was false.\n",
    "\n",
    "More examples\n",
    "\n",
    "Spam email goes into inbox\n",
    "\n",
    "Fraud transaction is marked as normal\n",
    "\n",
    "Cancer patient is predicted as healthy\n",
    "\n",
    "Summary Table\n",
    "Actual\tPredicted\tResult\n",
    "Positive\tPositive\tTrue Positive (TP)\n",
    "Negative\tNegative\tTrue Negative (TN)\n",
    "Negative\tPositive\tFalse Positive (FP)\n",
    "Positive\tNegative\tFalse Negative (FN)\n",
    "Easy Trick to Remember\n",
    "Step 1: Check whether prediction is correct or wrong\n",
    "\n",
    "True = correct\n",
    "\n",
    "False = wrong\n",
    "\n",
    "Step 2: Check what the model predicted\n",
    "\n",
    "Positive = predicted positive\n",
    "\n",
    "Negative = predicted negative\n",
    "\n",
    "So:\n",
    "\n",
    "True Positive = correct positive\n",
    "\n",
    "True Negative = correct negative\n",
    "\n",
    "False Positive = wrong positive\n",
    "\n",
    "False Negative = wrong negative\n",
    "\n",
    "Full Example Using Disease Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose a hospital tests whether patients have a disease.\n",
    "\n",
    "Patient\tActual\tPredicted\tResult\n",
    "A\tDisease\tDisease\tTP\n",
    "B\tNo Disease\tNo Disease\tTN\n",
    "C\tNo Disease\tDisease\tFP\n",
    "D\tDisease\tNo Disease\tFN\n",
    "Explanation\n",
    "\n",
    "A: model correctly found disease → TP\n",
    "\n",
    "B: model correctly said healthy → TN\n",
    "\n",
    "C: model wrongly said disease → FP\n",
    "\n",
    "D: model missed disease → FN\n",
    "\n",
    "Full Example Using Spam Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose an email classifier checks whether an email is spam.\n",
    "\n",
    "Email\tActual\tPredicted\tResult\n",
    "Email 1\tSpam\tSpam\tTP\n",
    "Email 2\tNot Spam\tNot Spam\tTN\n",
    "Email 3\tNot Spam\tSpam\tFP\n",
    "Email 4\tSpam\tNot Spam\tFN\n",
    "Explanation\n",
    "\n",
    "TP: spam correctly caught\n",
    "\n",
    "TN: genuine email correctly allowed\n",
    "\n",
    "FP: genuine email wrongly put into spam\n",
    "\n",
    "FN: spam email missed and comes to inbox\n",
    "\n",
    "Full Example Using Fraud Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose a bank model detects fraud.\n",
    "\n",
    "Transaction\tActual\tPredicted\tResult\n",
    "T1\tFraud\tFraud\tTP\n",
    "T2\tNormal\tNormal\tTN\n",
    "T3\tNormal\tFraud\tFP\n",
    "T4\tFraud\tNormal\tFN\n",
    "Explanation\n",
    "\n",
    "TP: fraud successfully detected\n",
    "\n",
    "TN: genuine transaction allowed\n",
    "\n",
    "FP: genuine transaction wrongly blocked\n",
    "\n",
    "FN: fraud missed\n",
    "\n",
    "Which one is important in different scenarios?\n",
    "\n",
    "This depends on business problem.\n",
    "\n",
    "Scenario 1: Medical Diagnosis\n",
    "\n",
    "TP: sick patient correctly identified\n",
    "\n",
    "TN: healthy patient correctly identified\n",
    "\n",
    "FP: healthy person wrongly told sick\n",
    "\n",
    "FN: sick person wrongly told healthy\n",
    "\n",
    "Most dangerous:\n",
    "\n",
    "Usually FN is more dangerous because disease is missed.\n",
    "\n",
    "Scenario 2: Spam Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "TP: spam caught\n",
    "\n",
    "TN: genuine mail allowed\n",
    "\n",
    "FP: real mail sent to spam\n",
    "\n",
    "FN: spam reaches inbox\n",
    "\n",
    "Most dangerous:\n",
    "\n",
    "Often FP is more harmful because important real emails may be lost.\n",
    "\n",
    "Scenario 3: Fraud Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "TP: fraud caught\n",
    "\n",
    "TN: real transaction allowed\n",
    "\n",
    "FP: real transaction blocked\n",
    "\n",
    "FN: fraud passes through\n",
    "\n",
    "Most dangerous:\n",
    "\n",
    "Often FN is more dangerous because actual fraud is missed.\n",
    "\n",
    "Scenario 4: Face Unlock System\n",
    "\n",
    "TP: authorized user allowed\n",
    "\n",
    "TN: unauthorized user blocked\n",
    "\n",
    "FP: unauthorized user gets access\n",
    "\n",
    "FN: authorized user gets denied\n",
    "\n",
    "Most dangerous:\n",
    "\n",
    "Usually FP is more dangerous because wrong person gets access.\n",
    "\n",
    "Visual Confusion Matrix\n",
    "                    Predicted\n",
    "                Positive   Negative\n",
    "Actual Positive     TP         FN\n",
    "Actual Negative     FP         TN\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the most standard way to remember it.\n",
    "\n",
    "Beginner-Friendly Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Think like this:\n",
    "\n",
    "TP\n",
    "\n",
    "Model says “Yes”\n",
    "Actual is also “Yes”\n",
    "✅ Correct\n",
    "\n",
    "TN\n",
    "\n",
    "Model says “No”\n",
    "Actual is also “No”\n",
    "✅ Correct\n",
    "\n",
    "FP\n",
    "\n",
    "Model says “Yes”\n",
    "Actual is actually “No”\n",
    "❌ False alarm\n",
    "\n",
    "FN\n",
    "\n",
    "Model says “No”\n",
    "Actual is actually “Yes”\n",
    "❌ Missed case\n",
    "\n",
    "Real-Life Analogy: Security Guard\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose a security guard checks whether a person is a thief.\n",
    "\n",
    "TP: thief is caught correctly\n",
    "\n",
    "TN: innocent person is allowed correctly\n",
    "\n",
    "FP: innocent person is wrongly caught\n",
    "\n",
    "FN: thief is allowed to go\n",
    "\n",
    "This analogy helps a lot in interviews.\n",
    "\n",
    "Interview Answer\n",
    "\n",
    "In binary classification, there are four outcomes. True Positive means the model correctly predicts a positive case, such as correctly detecting fraud. True Negative means it correctly predicts a negative case, such as allowing a genuine transaction. False Positive means it incorrectly predicts positive for a negative case, such as flagging a genuine email as spam. False Negative means it incorrectly predicts negative for a positive case, such as missing a real disease case. The importance of FP and FN depends on the business problem.\n",
    "\n",
    "Extra: Metrics built from TP, TN, FP, FN\n",
    "\n",
    "These four values are used to calculate important metrics:\n",
    "\n",
    "Accuracy = (TP+TN)/(TP+TN+FP+FN)\n",
    "\n",
    "Precision = TP/(TP+FP)\n",
    "\n",
    "Recall = TP/(TP+FN)\n",
    "\n",
    "Specificity = TN/(TN+FP)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "F1 Score = F1 = 2*((Precision*Recall)/(Precision+Recall))\n",
    "\n",
    "One-line Memory Trick\n",
    "\n",
    "TP = correctly said yes\n",
    "\n",
    "TN = correctly said no\n",
    "\n",
    "FP = wrongly said yes\n",
    "\n",
    "FN = wrongly said no\n",
    "\n",
    "Super Short Revision\n",
    "Term\tMeaning\n",
    "TP\tActual positive, predicted positive\n",
    "TN\tActual negative, predicted negative\n",
    "FP\tActual negative, predicted positive\n",
    "FN\tActual positive, predicted negative"
   ]
